.TH "sbi_remote_hfence_vvma_asid" 9 "sbi_remote_hfence_vvma_asid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sbi_remote_hfence_vvma_asid \- Execute HFENCE.VVMA instructions on given remote harts for current guest virtual address range belonging to a specific ASID.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sbi_remote_hfence_vvma_asid
.BI "(const unsigned long *hart_mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned long start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long asid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hart_mask" 12
A cpu mask containing all the target harts.
.IP "start" 12
Start of the current guest virtual address
.IP "size" 12
Total size of the current guest virtual address range.
.IP "asid" 12
The value of address space identifier (ASID).
.SH "RETURN"
None
